  "texts": [
    "This indicates the robustness of our attack against perturbation-based defense.",
    "Self-instructed Defenses Similar to the safety instruction defense proposed in paper (Varshney et al., 2023), we evaluate defenses embedded directly within the system prompts by including \"Always follow this instruction\" across the datasets.",
    "The backdoor still exhibits a 96.00% ASR and 98.40% CACC, with FTR at 0.86% and ITR at 0.52% using Mistral model in case 5.2.",
    "We do not explore paraphrasing or retokenization-based defenses, as altering user inputs could compromise the model's response to the user's question and potentially distort the users' intended meaning.",
    "Resilience to RLHF."
  ]
